&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;Greenlight is a Canadian-founded forward-thinking and rapidly growing technology services firm&amp;nbsp;specializing in Robotic Process Automation (RPA) Consulting. We have a high-performance mindset&amp;nbsp;with a culture that is driven by our values, including kindness, ownership, transparency, and fairness.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;This drives a collaborative workplace where we have fun, keep integrity in our work, and authenticity&amp;nbsp;every step of the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes a star at Greenlight?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;Inherently inquisitive and driven&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;Innovative, detailed, and process-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;Passionate about all things Technology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;p4&quot;&gt;Outstanding communication and presentation skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p5&quot;&gt;We are seeking an RPA Developer to design, build and maintain automation solutions for a&amp;nbsp;major client project. You will work closely with developers, business analysts and project&amp;nbsp;managers to deliver high-quality, scalable automations. This role focuses on hands-on&amp;nbsp;development and delivery (development, testing, deployment and hypercare).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p3&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Design, develop, test and deploy UiPath automations and associated low-code solutions&amp;nbsp;(Power Automate / Power Apps where applicable).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Implement Document Understanding (DU) / IXP pipelines for document classification,&amp;nbsp;extraction and validation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Integrate automations with external systems (APIs, databases, web applications, CUDL-like&amp;nbsp;platforms).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Build transaction-based processes using REFramework and Orchestrator queues; implement&amp;nbsp;retry/backoff, poison-item handling and monitoring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Produce technical artifacts: PDD/SDD, runbooks, test cases and release notes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Participate in code reviews, version control and ALM practices to promote Dev → Test → Prod&amp;nbsp;deployments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Troubleshoot production issues, support hypercare and handover to support teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Collaborate with stakeholders to clarify requirements and deliver business value.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s7&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What will you need to succeed:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• 3–6 years of professional experience in RPA development, with strong hands-on UiPath&amp;nbsp;experience (development in Studio and use of Orchestrator).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Solid experience with REFramework, queue-based transaction processing and robust&amp;nbsp;exception handling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Experience integrating with APIs and databases; familiarity with data mapping and&amp;nbsp;error-handling patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Familiarity with basic scripting/programming; Python experience preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Experience producing technical documentation (PDD/SDD, runbooks) and participating in&amp;nbsp;code review/ALM processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;• Strong problem-solving skills, attention to detail and ability to communicate with technical&amp;nbsp;and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
